junior  and  500 as a senior in the Advanced ROTC course  Gain tuition assistance and great leadership skills through this program  Scholarships 3 year and 2 year National Guard Scholarships are available through the Army ROTC department  The scholarship pays full tuition and fees  most books  plus a monthly living allowance  Eligible Army ROTC cadets can apply for these scholarship during January of their freshmen and sophomore years  For more information  please contact  Maj  Corey Stavinoha Phone   540  464 7187 Email  stavinohacj vmi edu Mr  Thomas Atkinson Phone   540  464 7680 Email  atkinsonte vmi edu VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Army National Guard    Virginia Military Institute   Army National Guard                        skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportun